<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JAN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nutmeg and mace prices were strong again, reflecting a lack of offers from
Indonesia. East Indian prices increased, so that finally West Indian
offerings became competitive and stocks began to be reduced. The cassia
season is now over and prices have slowly begun to decline. Further
decreases can be expected until March/April, when purchases begin to be made
for the autumn grindings. Mexican pimento is sold out, leaving Jamaica as
more or less the only supplier. Cloves prices remain depressed. Grenada
nutmeg prices were: suns Dollars 1,875 a tonne; and guns Dollars 1,475. Mace
no2 was offered at Dollars 2,750 a tonne. Indonesia abcd nutmegs were
fetching Dollars 1,875 a tonne; ss Dollars 1,800; and bwp Dollars 1,650. The
mace price was Dollars 2,950 a tonne.
</TEXT>
