<DATELINE>
   PARIS, LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Union des Assurances de Paris, France's biggest insurance company which has
for some time hoped to expand into the UK non-life insurance market,
yesterday confirmed that it was in negotiations with a possible acquisition
target. It refused, however, to comment on the company's identity.
'We have made contact with a UK company but it would be premature to say
more on the matter as our discussions are still at a preliminary stage,' the
company said. UAP hoped to conclude a UK deal before the end of 1994 but it
