FT  29 JAN 94 / Trustees silent on plan for gallery
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The trustees of the National Gallery of Scotland declined to comment last
night after meeting to discuss a controversial plan to create a new gallery
of Scottish art in Glasgow. This would entail closing the Scottish National
Portrait Gallery in Edinburgh.
