the House of Lords that it had the final say on the issue, which could
require legislation.
It suggested that the trustees were 'putting the cart before the horse' in
deciding to go ahead with the project and choosing its location without
formally submitting its plans to the government.
Before the meeting Mr Angus Grossart, chairman of the trustees, said they
would be 'progressing' their formal submission.
