suggested the COPPER market would not be troubled by Codelco's trading
losses and prices tested Dollars 1,890 a tonne again before three-months
metal closed at Dollars 1,883.50, up Dollars 11. GOLD drifted lower amid
rumours that Venezuela's financially troubled Banco Latino might have 10 to
15 tonnes to dump.
