FT  28 JAN 94 / International Company News: Results push McDonald's stock to
52-week high
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Wall Street celebrated McDonald's Corporation's Dollars 1bn 1993 earnings by
pushing the hamburger chain's stock to its highest price in a year, Dollars
60.
The world's largest fast-food company reported fourth-quarter net income of
Dollars 264.5m or 72 cents per share, on sales of Dollars 6.1bn. That
compares to net income of Dollars 227.9m or 61 cents per share on sales of
Dollars 5.7bn a year ago.
For the year, McDonald's had net income of Dollars 1.08bn or Dollars 2.91
per share on sales of Dollars 24bn, up from fiscal 1992's earnings of
Dollars 958m or Dollars 2.60 per share on sales of Dollars 21.8bn.
The company added 900 restaurants to its 14,000-unit chain during 1993.
McDonald's does not disclose comparative results excluding new restaurant
additions.
Operating income within the US grew at a moderate 4 per cent for the year
and 5 per cent in the fourth quarter, while operating income in McDonald's
markets outside the US grew by 9 per cent for the year and 10 per cent in
the fourth quarter.
A large portion of the company's restaurant expansion occurred outside the
US in 1993, leading to the higher overseas growth rate.
