<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Louis Newmark cuts loss
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax losses at Louis Newmark for the half year ended October 2 were cut
from Pounds 888,000 to Pounds 638,000.
With the second half usually the stronger, losses are expected to fall
further.
Turnover for the company, which has interests in the manufacture of
electronic instruments, machining and watch importing, advanced to Pounds
12.2m, against Pounds 10.7m which included Pounds 665,000 from discontinued
activities.
Sales from continuing operations rose 22 per cent with a sharp recovery in
the capital goods businesses.
The company said that the pension fund had moved into deficit and that its
annual provision would have to be increased by Pounds 160,000. This was
reflected pro rata in the interim results.
Losses per share came out at 15.2p (30p).
