<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Warner Estate at Pounds 7.3m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Warner Estate Holdings, the property investment company, yesterday announced
pre-tax profits of Pounds 7.3m for the year to September 1993, up from a
restated Pounds 4.12m in 1992.
Turnover fell to Pounds 11m (Pounds 12.2m) as a result of a decline in
property trading activity. A final dividend of 7.35p makes an 11p (10.5p)
total.
Earnings also amounted to 11p and net asset value was Pounds 129.2m at the
year end, or 266p (247p) a share.
The company has subsequently raised Pounds 5m from the sale of the Catford
Centre, and invested Pounds 17.4m in a mixed commercial property portfolio.
